        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 14 at 4:55AM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 455 AM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Chesterfield, or 8
miles northeast of Little River Canyon National Preserve, moving east
at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Pea sized hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to exposed surfaces is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Summerville, Lyerly, Menlo, James H. Floyd State Park, and Berryton.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately.</instruction>
